JavaScript - Scripting the furture.

Rise of JavaScript:

1995: JavaScript, then named LiveScript, was created at Netscape by Brenden Eich.
.
.
. Battling browsers war and competitors (VBScript, Java Applets)
.
.
2004: Google released Gmail (beta) powered with AJAX (Async JavaScript and XML).
.
.
2006: jQuery help JavaScript conquer browser war.
.
.
2008: JavaScript Good Parts Book by Doughlas Crockford.
.
.
2009: NodeJS runs JavaScript on server
.
.
2010: Go HTML5 way. No more Flash.
.
.
2011: Rich Client side Apps using AngularJS, EmberJS, KnockoutJS, MeteorJS
.
.
2012: Frontend Tool chain for faster development
.
.
2015: ECMAScript 6 is coming to empower Web like never before.



